==>OBSERVATION: Performance Ring
This is the arena's oval-shaped performance ring. The rope ladder above your head has been tangled around the platform from which it hangs.

Just west lies the entrance to a large, round cage that completely encircles the second of the two rings. To the south the big top's vaulted wing leads out into the open air. The arena's rickety grandstands rise steeply north and east.

Craning your neck upward, you see Mahler standing on the platform above the rope ladder. He is holding the limp form of a small girl under one arm.

Mr. Munrab, pacing pitifully back and forth across the ring, is a complete wreck.

A roustabout stands nearby.
