Performance Ring

The safety net is being held by the motley circle of Mr. Munrab, the roustabout, and Comrade Thumb.

You can see a lion stand, a spreadsheet, a scrap of newsprint, a ribbon, a ransom note, a trade card, a veil, a dress-suit combination, a shawl-jacket combo and a crowbar here.

Just now a gaggle of circus performers -- Andrew Jenny, Chuckles, Rimshaw the Incomparable, Billy Monday, Gottfried Wilhelm von Katzenjammer -- appear through the wings. Quickly assessing the situation, the group seems to suddenly, gut-wrenchingly accept the burden of responsibility for the calamity that has occurred. Their immediate reaction is the instinct to help, and each grabs part of the net.
